        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Bump: The ability to exclude buffers based on their filetype is critical. Otherwise `:mksession` will save stuff that can't be restored, making it useless in most scenarios.\r\n\r\nThis feature would allow session manager plugins to set filetype nofile to the files that we are not supposed to save in a session.\r\n\r\nCurrently the workarounds are:\r\n\r\n* [Deleting from the GUI anything `nofile` before running `:mksession`](https://github.com/Shatur/neovim-session-manager/blob/df544e17798dd0e6e33ecf0991dfde9174367837/lua/session_manager/utils.lua#L78) → Not ideal, we have to do it before closing nvim, otherwise it will close buffers the user may still need. But this approach can cause the user to lose the session on power loss.\r\n* [Having your own implementation of mksession](https://github.com/stevearc/resession.nvim). → Not ideal, it will fragment the ecosystem.\r\n",
